[FEN "r1b1k2r/1pQpnppp/p4q2/4p3/1n2P3/2NB4/PPP2PPP/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 0 10"]
[PlyCount "7"]
[GameId "2141525848216658"]

{This is the main line of the 8. [Qc7] variation, one where Black can immediately break out with the most important and most common of the potential pawn breaks available to the Löwenthal Logician.} 10... d5 $1 {[%cal Gb4d3,Gd5d4,Gc8e6,Ge8g8,Ga8c8] Liberation! Black may simply continue development with ...[O-O], ... [Be6] and ...[Rc8], but the ideas of ...[d4], to disrupt the knight on [c3], and ... [Nxd3]+, to rid White of the bishop-pair, are also important ones.} 11. exd5 Nexd5 {[%cal Gb4d3,Gd5c7] Continuing to activate and now we'd like to damage White's structure on [d3] should the queen immediately retreat.} 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gd5c7] This important position is the subject of chapter 2B. White does have the two bishops, but the knight on [d5] is also a fine piece.} 13. Qc5 Be6 {[%cal Ga8c8,Gf6e7] Black will continue with ...[Rc8] and, if needed to help the king, ...[Qe7], leaving us with an easy and active game.} *

