[GameId "2141525848265811"]

{White hasn't handled the opening in the best possible fashion and Black can already take over, all thanks to the key pawn break.} 9... d5 $1 {[%cal Gd5e4] Threatening to win a pawn on [e4] while helping the remaining queenside pieces spring to life.} 10. exd5 Nxd5 {[%csl Gc2][%cal Gd5b4,Gc6d4,Gc8f5,Ge8c8]} (10... Nxd5 {It's only move 10 and already Black is for choice. The immediate threat is} 11. Z0 Ndb4 {, and if} 12. Na3 Nd4 {, (increasing the pressure against [c2]. Meanwhile, the light-squared bishop is en route to [f5] or just [e6], and Black can very much consider aggressive ideas involving early queenside castling.)}) *

[Event "The Killer Löwenthal Sicilian"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
