[White "Key Ideas in the Löwenthal Sicilian"]
[Black "The ...d5 Break Part III"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "r1b1k2r/1pQpnppp/p5q1/4p3/2PnP3/3B4/PP3PPP/RNB2RK1 b kq - 0 11"]
[PlyCount "7"]
[GameId "2141525848274004"]

{This is an 8. [Qc7] variation gone wrong for White and already Black can secure a pretty powerful initiative with our favourite pawn break.} 11... d5 $1 {[%cal Gd5e4,Gc8h3] Boom! This is a dream scenario for the light-squared bishop which threatens to head straight out to [h3].} 12. cxd5 $2 (12. f3 $5 dxc4 13. Qxc4 Bh3 {Threatening mate, of course.} 14. Rf2 Nxf3+ {Winning a clear pawn, although 12. [f3] and this line is still the best defence that the engines can see.}) 12... Bh3 {[%csl Gg1][%cal Gg6g2] With a certain threat once again.} 13. g3 Nf3+ {[%csl Gg1]} 14. Kh1 Qh5 {[%csl Gh1][%cal Gh3g4,Gh3f1,Gh5h2] Black is already winning with both ...[Bxf1] and ...[Bg4] such sizeable threats.} *

[Event "The Killer Löwenthal Sicilian"]
[Site "?"]
