1. e4 c5 {The Sicilian Defence - an excellent, fighting response to 1. [e4] at all levels.} 2. Nf3 {In this course, we'll be focussing on how to react when White heads into main line Open Sicilian waters with this then 3. [d4].} Nc6 {[%csl Gd4,Ge5] By no means forced, of course, but sensible development and a key component of the Löwenthal variation, the line of the Open Sicilian with which we hope to confuse White. Already, Black is ready for a dark-square approach in the centre, aiming to control the [d4]- and [e5]-squares.} 3. d4 {[%cal Rd4c5,Rd4d5] The Open Sicilian.} cxd4 {A pretty essential exchange, as well as key component of the Löwenthal move order.} 4. Nxd4 {White's main move, setting up the Open Sicilian.} e5 {[%csl Gd4] Our key Löwenthal central strike, refusing to allow the knight to settle on [d4].} 5. Nxc6 {[%csl Rd8]} bxc6 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gg8f6,Gf8c5] Recapturing towards the centre while taking control of [d5], an important square which initially belongs to White in the main line Lowenthal. We're now all set to develop in fairly aggressive fashion with ...[Nf6] and ...[Bc5].} 6. Bc4 {White may hope for some pressure against [f7], but that is easily dealt with.} Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4] Developing with tempo.} 7. Nc3 Bc5 $5 {[%csl Gc5][%cal Ge8g8,Gd7d6,Gc8e6] A less common approach compared to 7...[Bb4], if one we quite like. Black is now set to complete development with ...[O-O], ...[d6] and ...[Be6].} 8. O-O O-O {[%csl Gd5] Thanks to Black's control of [d5], it's not so easy for White to find a good plan here.} 9. Bg5 {Attempting to disrupt with a pin.} h6 {In most of our lines, it's rarely a bad idea to prod a bishop on [g5] straightaway so, thereby asking White: what was really your intention?} 10. Bh4 {Wisely preserving the bishop-pair.} Bd4 $1 {[%csl Gb2,Gc3,Ge5][%cal Ga8b8,Gd7d6,Gg7g5] A fine central post for the bishop, creating some pressure while covering [e5]. As we'll see further in chapter 6c, Black enjoys a comfortable game, with not just ...[d6], but ideas of ...[Rb8] and ...[g5] also high on the agenda.} *

