1. e4 c5 {The Sicilian Defence - an excellent, fighting response to 1. [e4] at all levels.} 2. Nf3 {In this course, we'll be focussing on how to react when White heads into main line Open Sicilian waters with this then 3. [d4].} Nc6 {[%csl Gd4,Ge5] By no means forced, of course, but sensible development and a key component of the Löwenthal variation, the line of the Open Sicilian with which we hope to confuse White. Already, Black is ready for a dark-square approach in the centre, aiming to control the [d4]- and [e5]-squares.} 3. d4 {[%cal Rd4c5,Rd4d5] The Open Sicilian.} cxd4 {A pretty essential exchange, as well as key component of the Löwenthal move order.} 4. Nxd4 {White's main move, setting up the Open Sicilian.} e5 {[%csl Gd4] Our key Löwenthal central strike, refusing to allow the knight to settle on [d4].} 5. Nb3 (5. Nb3 {Another not too active but sensible retreat, as White may angle for transposition to a sideline of the Sveshnikov after} Nf6 6. Nc3 Bb4 {. That's fine for Black, but we also don't have to play ball.}) 5... Bb4+ $5 {[%csl Ge1][%cal Gd7d6,Ga7a5]} (5... Bb4+ {Discombobulating and forcing White to make an early choice. Here} 6. Nc3 {has been surprisingly rare and note too that then we can simply continue development with} d6 {.}) (5... Bb4+ {Another concept worth noting is that of meeting} 6. Bd2 {in aggressive fashion with} a5 $5 {.}) 6. c3 {[%csl Rb4]} Be7 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gg8f6] Dropping the bishop back and now 7...[Nf6] will be slightly awkward for White as he no longer has [Nc3] available - another important point behind the check on [b4].} (6... Be7 {Admittedly,} 7. c4 {is possible, but after} Nf6 8. Nc3 Bb4 {the bishop returns with some force.}) 7. Bc4 Nf6 {[%csl Ge4] Threatening to annex the pawn.} 8. Qd3 d6 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gc8e6] Sensible development, looking to go ...[Be6] then get in ...[d5].} 9. Bg5 a6 $5 {[%cal Gb7b5,Gf6e4]} (9... a6 {A crafty little move which we'll cover further in chapter 6e. Black prepares ...b5 and also, by covering the b5-square, creates a radical idea in the centre:} 10. Z0 Nxe4 $5 {, and if} 11. Bxe7 Nxe7 {followed by ...[d5].}) *

