should be happy to see and Black has scored well from here.} Nxc2+ {[%csl Ge1][%cal Gc2e3] Discomforting the white king, if again a move not played with the intention of taking on [a1].} 14. Kd2 {[%cal Rd1c2]} Nxe3 $1 {[%csl Gd1]} ({An important bishop to remove, whereas after} 14... Nxa1 $2 15. Qc1 $1 Qb4+ 16. Kd1 {it's long been established that the black king is in somewhat more danger than the white one.}) 15. Qc1 $2 {[%cal Rc1c5,Rc1c8,Rc1c7]} Qd4+ $1 {[%csl Gd2]} 16. Bd3 Nd5 $1 {[%csl Gc7][%cal Gd4f2] A calm and strong retreat, taking the [c7]-square away from the white queen while threatening to take on [f2].} 17. Qxc8 Ngf6 $1 {[%cal Gh8c8,Gf6e4,Gd4b2] Black offers a second rook and already the initiative is an extremely dangerous one indeed.} 18. Qxb7+ Nd7 {[%cal Gh8b8,Gd4f2] Threatening ...[Rb8], as well as to take on [f2].} 19. Nc7 Nf4 {[%csl Gd3]} 20. Qe4 Qxb2+ {[%csl Gd2][%cal Gd7f6,Gh8d8] With ...[Nf6] followed by ...[Rd8]+ if required, White will be unable to hold back the black tide.} *

