should be happy to see and Black has scored well from here.} Nxc2+ {[%csl Ge1][%cal Gc2e3] Discomforting the white king, if again a move not played with the intention of taking on [a1].} 14. Kd2 {[%cal Rd1c2]} Nxe3 $1 {[%csl Gd1]} ({An important bishop to remove, whereas after} 14... Nxa1 $2 15. Qc1 $1 Qb4+ 16. Kd1 {it's long been established that the black king is in somewhat more danger than the white one.}) 15. Qb3 $2 {[%csl Re3]} Nxf1+ {[%csl Gd2]} 16. Rhxf1 Nh6 $1 {[%csl Ga8,Gd2][%cal Gh8d8] The right square for the knight, as well as a move which leaves Black threatening ...[Rd8]+ and with far too much for the exchange.} 17. Qa3+ $2 Kf6 {[%csl Gd2][%cal Gh8d8,Gc8e6] This is why the knight went to [h6], not [f6].} 18. Qf3+ Qxf3 19. gxf3 Bh3 {[%csl Ga8,Gf1] Thanks to the double-attack, Black will emerge material in front.} *

