should be happy to see and Black has scored well from here.} Nxc2+ {[%csl Ge1][%cal Gc2e3] Discomforting the white king, if again a move not played with the intention of taking on [a1].} 14. Kd2 {[%cal Rd1c2]} Nxe3 $1 {[%csl Gd1]} ({An important bishop to remove, whereas after} 14... Nxa1 $2 15. Qc1 $1 Qb4+ 16. Kd1 {it's long been established that the black king is in somewhat more danger than the white one.}) 15. fxe3 {Sensibly recapturing.} Nf6 {[%csl Gh8][%cal Gf6g4,Gh8d8] Preparing to deploy the rook while also giving Black ideas with ...[Ng4].} 16. Qf3 $2 Qb4+ 17. Kc2 Bg4 {[%csl Gc2,Gf3][%cal Gh8c8,Gg4f3] White was unable to save both king and queen, so resigned here in R.Sax-A.Chow, Illinois 1992.} *

