is ...[Rd1].} 26. Be2 Rd5 $1 {Sensibly making the rook safe, and with tempo.} 27. Bxg4 Qxg4 28. Qf2+ Kg6 {Black has just two pawns for the rook, but threatens to check on [d1] then [h3] and just appears to be doing pretty well.} 29. Rc1 Qg5 30. Re1 Bh3 $1 {Immobilising the kingside pieces while preparing to break through with ...[Rd2]. By now it should be clear that Black is just doing pretty well.}) *

