 hxg6 {[%csl Gh8][%cal Gg8f6] And so the rook on [h8] becomes a factor without having had to move, while Black is all set to complete development with ...[Nf6], or even ...[f5] and ...[Nf6] to obtain an outpost on [e4].} 20. c3 {[%csl Rd4]} Ne6 $5 {[%csl Gc7,Gf4]} ({A new idea to force the pace, not that there's too much wrong with} 20... Nc6 21. O-O Nf6 {.}) 21. Nxe6 Kxe6 {Keeping Black's structure intact ahead of deploying the f-pawn.} 22. O-O f5 {[%csl Gd8,Ge4][%cal Ge6f7,Gg8f6] (The ending looks fine for Black, who already has one well-placed rook, can now easily retreat the king to f7 when checked, and wouldn't mind getting in ...Nf6-e4 for the record, 22...f6!? followed by ...[Ne7] also seems fine.)} *

