d, and if} 17. Nc5 Bc8 $1 {to retain an important piece followed by ...[b6].}) {Finally, with the bishop now in play, Black is all set to force the pace with 16...Nc6 as then 17.Qxb5 axb5 18.Nb6 wouldn't lead anywhere after 18...Ra6 .} 16. Nc5 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Rc5e6]} Bc8 $5 {[%cal Gb7b6] Not forced, but it makes sense to keep everything covered while threatening ... [b6].} 17. Na4 Be6 {[%cal Ge7c6] Offering a repetition, one which we can see White accepting.} *

