e with Nb6 and Rac1 and here} 17. Nb6 {can be dealt with comfortably enough by} Rb8 18. Nd5 Kd7 {. Black also gets ready to contest the c-file with ...[Ke7] and ...[Rhc8].}) 17. Nc5 Ke7 {[%cal Gh8c8]} 18. Rac1 Rhc8 {[%cal Ga6a5,Gf7f6] Completing the mini-plan. Black may now stabilise the centre with ...[f6], which possibly also hints at kingside expansion in the not-too-distant future, or consider expanding on the queenside with ...[a5].} 19. Rc2 Nd8 $1 {[%cal Ge6d7,Gd8e6] An important retreat to note as Black avoids becoming uncomfortably pinned down the c-file and can now regroup with ...[Bd7] and ...[Ne6]. There shouldn't be anything to fear here.} *

