prevent White from continuing development with 10. [Nc3].} d5 $1 {[%cal Gd5e4,Gd5d4]} (9... d5 {Of course, and now} 10. Nc3 $4 d4 {would not be at all wise.}) 10. exd5 Nxd5 {[%cal Gd5e3] Naturally Black recaptures so, getting ready to remove a certain unopposed bishop on [e3].} 11. Bc5 $2 {There's no time for this. White should prefer to allow the exchange on [e3] and so maintain approximate equality.} Nd4 $1 {[%cal Gd4c2,Gd5f4]} (11... Nd4 {Not the only good move, but our classic attack on c2 isn't so easy for White to meet in view of} 12. Bd3 Nf4 {.}) 12. Bxd4 exd4 {[%csl Ge1][%cal Gf6e5,Gd5f4,Gc8e6,Gc8g4,Gc8f5] With 13...[Qe5]+ imminent followed by ...[Nf4] or developing the bishop from [c8], Black is already somewhat for choice.} *

