13. Nxb5 $1 {is a little annoying.}) 13. Rfd1 Ng4 $5 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gg4e5,Gg4e3] With ...[O-O] and ...[Nge5] on the way, as well as the threat of ...[Nxe3], Black had taken charge of the position and was a clear pawn up in Poulheim-Van den Bos, correspondence 2012.} *

